{"TopicId":221459,"ForumId":208,"TopicTitle":"Continuous fireball follows craft","CreatedByName":"PicoSpace","CreatedById":224964,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T14:33:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"PicoSpace","CreatedById":224964,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T14:33:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win 10 Pro | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A05800X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A03070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E64 CL14\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay here is a fun one,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter a launch a \u201Cfireball\u201D continues to follow the craft through the whole mission. It has its only velocity profile relative to the active vessel (and Kerbal EVA) but it\u2019s clearly a function of the vessel\u2019s velocity (or acceleration) profile.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nvideo is snippets of its existences throughout the flight to show various states. I can post or provide an unabridged video if required.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/SPT3iRW8TrM?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Friendly Kraken Fire Ball in KSP2 For Science! Bug Report\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-20T19:27:06Z\u0022 title=\u002212/20/2023 07:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 20\u0022\u003EDecember 20, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shiny55","CreatedById":227198,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-17T21:39:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0/ | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0? | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0? | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA series of explosions, starting when on the launch pad (before engines are started) and continuing, sometimes behind, sometimes ahead of vessel.\u00A0 Continue when switching away from vessel (e.g. to mission control), also visible on old vessels when switching to them via tracking station.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-20T16:28:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/227198-shiny55/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022227198\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/227198-shiny55/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Shiny55\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n